1️⃣ COI – RFO Decision

✅ Use Case Name

Review and Submit RFO Decision for COI (Endorse / Refer Back)

⸻

✅ Description

RFO users should be able to review the COI assessment in read-only mode, navigate across stages, and submit their decision by endorsing or referring back the assessment.

⸻

✅ System Behavior

🔹 Navigation & Visibility
	•	RFO users can navigate across all assessment stages in read-only mode
	•	Stage 3a is visible only to RFO users
	•	Stage 3b is visible only to PM / 1LOD users
	•	The UI displays both stages as “Stage 3” for all users

⸻

🔹 User Actions
	•	Endorse the assessment
	•	Refer back the assessment (mandatory comments required)
	•	Add comments (optional for endorse)

⸻

🔹 Decision Logic
	•	If any RFO selects Refer Back → Status = Refer Back
	•	If all RFOs endorse → Status = Endorsed by RFO
	•	If at least one RFO is pending and no Refer Back exists → Status = Pending

⸻

🔹 Rules
	•	Each RFO submits decision independently
	•	System must not auto-decide based on other RFO actions

⸻

🔹 Validation
	•	Mandatory questions must be completed before endorsement
	•	Refer Back requires mandatory comments

⸻

🔹 Audit & Tracking
	•	All actions (endorse, refer back, comments) are logged with user and timestamp

⸻

🔹 Progress Tracking
	•	Visual progress indicator is displayed
	•	Completed steps are clearly marked
	•	Remaining steps are visible

⸻

✅ Target Output

RFO is able to:
	•	Navigate assessment stages in read-only mode
	•	View responses provided by PM
	•	Provide comments
	•	Submit decision (Endorse / Refer Back)

System should:
	•	Validate inputs before submission
	•	Update status based on RFO decisions
	•	Route assessment to PM if referred back
	•	Move to next stage if endorsed by all
	•	Capture all actions in audit logs

⸻

