3️⃣ FRA – RFO Decision (Country Coverage)

✅ Use Case Name

Review and Submit RFO Decision for FRA – Country Coverage

⸻

✅ Description

RFO users should be able to review the Fraud Risk Assessment (FRA) for country coverage and submit their decision along with required inputs.

⸻

✅ System Behavior

🔹 Navigation & Visibility
	•	Read-only navigation across stages
	•	Stage 4a is visible only to RFO users
	•	Stage 4b is visible only to PM / 1LOD users
	•	The UI displays both stages as “Stage 4”

⸻

🔹 User Actions
	•	Endorse assessment
	•	Refer back assessment (mandatory comments required)
	•	Provide comments and justification

⸻

🔹 FRA-Specific Inputs
	•	Recommendation and Conclusion
	•	Challenge details
	•	Risk Framework Owner
	•	Status (Not started / In progress / Completed)

⸻

🔹 Decision Logic
	•	If any RFO selects Refer Back → Status = Refer Back
	•	If all RFOs endorse → Status = Endorsed by RFO
	•	If at least one RFO is pending and no Refer Back exists → Status = Pending

⸻

🔹 Validation
	•	Mandatory inputs must be completed before endorsement
	•	Refer Back requires mandatory comments
	•	Comment limit enforced (5000 characters)

⸻

🔹 Audit & Tracking
	•	All actions logged with user and timestamp

⸻

🔹 Progress Tracking
	•	Visual indicators displayed
	•	Completed steps marked
	•	Remaining steps visible

⸻

✅ Target Output

RFO is able to:
	•	Review FRA assessment
	•	Provide inputs and comments
	•	Submit decision

System should:
	•	Validate inputs
	•	Update status
	•	Route assessment accordingly
	•	Maintain audit logs

⸻

